#. Tag: title
#: glossary.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr "Sõnastik"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this chapter you will find an explanation of most of the <quote>uncommon</"
"quote> words that are used in the handbook."
msgstr ""
"Selles peatükis selgitame kõige <quote>ebatavalisemaid</quote> mõisteid, "
"mida käsiraamat sisaldab."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "degrees"
msgstr "kraadid"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Degrees are units to measure angles or turns. A full turn is 360 degrees, a "
"half turn 180 degrees and a quarter turn 90 degrees. The commands "
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput>, <userinput>turnright</userinput> and "
"<userinput>direction</userinput> need an input in degrees."
msgstr ""
"Kraadid mõõdavad nurka ehk pöörde ulatust. Täispööre on 360 kraadi, "
"järelikult poolpööre 180 ja veerandpööre 90 kraadi. Käskude "
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput>, <userinput>turnright</userinput> ja "
"<userinput>direction</userinput> sisend peab olema antud kraadides."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "input and output of commands"
msgstr "käskude sisend ja väljund"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some commands take input, some commands give output, some commands take "
"input <emphasis>and</emphasis> give output and some commands neither take "
"input nor give output."
msgstr ""
"Mõned käsud vajavad sisendit, mõned annavad väljundit, mõned vajavad "
"sisendit ja annavad väljundit ning mõned ei vaja sisendit ega anna ka mingit "
"väljundit."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some examples of commands that only take input are: <screen>\n"
"forward 50\n"
"pencolor 255,0,0\n"
"print \"Hello!\"\n"
"</screen> The <userinput>forward</userinput> command takes <userinput>50</"
"userinput> as input. <userinput>forward</userinput> needs this input to know "
"how many <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> it should go "
"forward. <userinput>pencolor</userinput> takes a color as input and "
"<userinput>print</userinput> takes a string (a piece of text) as input. "
"Please note that the input can also be a container. The next example "
"illustrates this:"
msgstr ""
"Mõned näited ainult sisendiga käskudest: <screen>\n"
"forward 50\n"
"pencolor 255,0,0\n"
"print \"tere!\"\n"
"</screen> Käsk <userinput>forward</userinput> võtab sisendiks <userinput>50</"
"userinput>. <userinput>forward</userinput> vajab seda sisendit määramaks, "
"mitu <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pikslit</glossterm> edasi liikuda. "
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> võtab sisendiks värvikoodi ja "
"<userinput>print</userinput> stringi. Pane tähele, et sisend võib olla ka "
"konteiner, nagu näha järgnevas näites:"

#. Tag: screen
#: glossary.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$x = 50\n"
"print $x\n"
"forward 50\n"
"$str = \"hello!\"\n"
"print $str"
msgstr ""
"$x = 50\n"
"print $x\n"
"forward 50\n"
"$str = \"tere!\"\n"
"print $str"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now some examples of commands that give output: <screen>\n"
"$x = ask \"Please type something and press OK... thanks!\"\n"
"$r = random 1,100\n"
"</screen> The <userinput>ask</userinput> command takes a string as input, "
"and outputs the number or string that is entered. As you can see, the output "
"of <userinput>ask</userinput> is stored in the container <userinput>x</"
"userinput>. The <userinput>random</userinput> command also gives output. In "
"this case it outputs a number between 1 and 100. The output of the random is "
"again stored in a container, named <userinput>r</userinput>. Note that the "
"containers <userinput>x</userinput> and <userinput>r</userinput> are not "
"used in the example code above."
msgstr ""
"Nüüd mõned näited väljundit andvate käskude kohta: <screen>\n"
"$x = ask \"Palun kirjuta midagi ja vajuta OK... aitäh!\"\n"
"$r = random 1,100\n"
"</screen> Käsk <userinput>ask</userinput> võtab stringi sisendiks ja annab "
"väljundiks sisestatud arvu või stringi. Nagu näha, on <userinput>ask</"
"userinput> väljund salvestatud konteineris <userinput>x</userinput>. Ka käsk "
"<userinput>random</userinput> annab väljundi. Antud juhul on väljundiks "
"number vahemikus 1 kuni 100. Ka see väljund on salvestatud konteinerisse, "
"milleks siin on <userinput>r</userinput>. Pane tähele, et konteinereid "
"<userinput>x</userinput> ja <userinput>r</userinput> ei ole kasutatud "
"eespool toodud näidiskoodis."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are also commands that neither need input nor give output. Here are "
"some examples:"
msgstr "Mõned käsud ei vaja sisendit ega anna ka väljundit, näiteks:"

#. Tag: screen
#: glossary.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"clear\n"
"penup"
msgstr ""
"clear\n"
"penup"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "intuitive highlighting"
msgstr "intuitiivne esiletõstmine"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is a feature of &kturtle; that makes coding even easier. With intuitive "
"highlighting the code that you write gets a color that indicates what type "
"of code it is. In the next list you will find the different types of code "
"and the color they get in <link linkend=\"the-editor\">the editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"See &kturtle;'i omadus muudab koodi kirjutamise veelgi kergemaks. "
"Esiletõstmine annab kirjutatud koodi osadele erinevad värvid, mis märgivad "
"seda, millist tüüpi koodiga kuskil tegemist on. Järgnevas tabelis on ära "
"toodud erinevad kooditüübid ja värv, millega selliseid osi näitab <link "
"linkend=\"the-editor\">redaktor</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: glossary.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "Different types of code and their highlight color"
msgstr "Erinevad kooditüübid ja nende esiletõstmise värv"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid "regular commands"
msgstr "tavalised käsud"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "dark blue"
msgstr "tumesinine"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular commands are described <link linkend=\"commands\">here</link>."
msgstr "Tavalisi käske kirjeldatakse <link linkend=\"commands\">siin</link>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "execution controlling commands"
msgstr "täitmist kontrollivad käsud"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "black (bold)"
msgstr "must (rasvane)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These special commands control execution, read more on them <link linkend="
"\"controlling-execution\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Nende spetsiaalsete käskude täitmist kontrollivate käskude kohta saab "
"põhjalikumalt lugeda <link linkend=\"controlling-execution\">siit</link>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "comments"
msgstr "kommentaarid"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:48 glossary.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "gray"
msgstr "hall"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lines that are commented start with a comment characters (#). These lines "
"are ignored when the code is executed. Comments allow the programmer to "
"explain a bit about his code or can be used to temporarily prevent a certain "
"piece of code from executing."
msgstr ""
"Kommenteeritud ridade alguses seisab vastav sümbol (#). Neid ridu koodi "
"täitmisel ignoreeritakse. Kommentaarid lubavad programmeerijal oma koodi "
"selgitada või siis ajutiselt teatud koodiosa täitmata jätta."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "brackets {, }"
msgstr "looksulud {, }"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "dark green (bold)"
msgstr "tumeroheline (rasvane)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Brackets are used to group portions of code. Brackets are often used "
"together with <link linkend=\"controlling-execution\">execution controllers</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"Nurksulge kasutatakse koodiosade grupeerimiseks. Tihtipeale pruugitakse neid "
"koos <link linkend=\"controlling-execution\">täitmise kontrolleritega</link>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "the <link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link> command"
msgstr "käsk <link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link>"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "light green (bold)"
msgstr "heleroheline (rasvane)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link> command is used to create new "
"commands."
msgstr "Käsuga <link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link> saab luua uusi käske."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "strings"
msgstr "stringid"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:63 glossary.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>red</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>punane</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Not much to say about (text) strings either, except that they always start "
"and end with the double quotes (\")."
msgstr ""
"Ega ka (teksti)stringide kohta pole palju muud öelda, kui et nende alguses "
"ja lõpus on alati topeltjutumärgid (\")."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "numbers"
msgstr "numbrid"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:68 glossary.docbook:73 glossary.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "dark red"
msgstr "tumepunane"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Numbers, well not much to say about them."
msgstr "Numbrid on numbrid, mis nende kohta ikka rohkem öelda..."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "boolean values"
msgstr "tõeväärtused"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are exactly two boolean values, namely: true and false."
msgstr "Tõeväärtusi on kõigest kaks: tõene (true) ja väär (false)."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "variables"
msgstr "muutujad"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "purple"
msgstr "purpurne"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start with a '$' and can contain numbers, strings or boolean values."
msgstr "Algavad märgiga '$' ja võivad sisaldada arve, stringe või tõeväärtusi."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "mathematical operators"
msgstr "matemaatilised tehted"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the mathematical operators: <userinput>+</userinput>, <userinput>-"
"</userinput>, <userinput>*</userinput>, <userinput>/</userinput> and "
"<userinput>^</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Matemaatilised tehted on järgmised: <userinput>+</userinput>, <userinput>-</"
"userinput>, <userinput>*</userinput>, <userinput>/</userinput> ja "
"<userinput>^</userinput>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "comparison operators"
msgstr "võrdlustehted"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "light blue (bold)"
msgstr "helesinine (rasvane)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the comparison operators: <userinput>==</userinput>, <userinput>!"
"=</userinput>, <userinput>&lt;</userinput>, <userinput>&gt;</userinput>, "
"<userinput>&lt;=</userinput> and <userinput>&gt;=</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Võrdlustehted on järgmised: <userinput>==</userinput>, <userinput>!=</"
"userinput>, <userinput>&lt;</userinput>, <userinput>&gt;</userinput>, "
"<userinput>&lt;=</userinput> ja <userinput>&gt;=</userinput>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "boolean operators"
msgstr "tõeväärtustehted"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "pink (bold)"
msgstr "roosa (rasvane)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the boolean operators: <userinput>and</userinput>, <userinput>or</"
"userinput> and <userinput>not</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Tõeväärtustehted on järgmised: <userinput>and</userinput>, <userinput>or</"
"userinput> ja <userinput>not</userinput>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "regular text"
msgstr "tavaline tekst"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:98 glossary.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "black"
msgstr "must"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "pixels"
msgstr "pikslid"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pixel is a dot on the screen. If you look very close you will see that the "
"screen of your monitor uses pixels. All images on the screen are built with "
"these pixels. A pixel is the smallest thing that can be drawn on the screen."
msgstr ""
"Piksel on punkt ekraanil. Kui vaatad väga teraselt, näed, et kogu sinu "
"monitori ekraan on piksleid täis. Kõik ekraanil olevad kujutised õigupoolest "
"pikslitest koosnevadki. Piksel ongi kõige väiksem asi, mida saab ekraanile "
"joonistada."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A lot of commands need a number of pixels as input. These commands are: "
"<userinput>forward</userinput>, <userinput>backward</userinput>, "
"<userinput>go</userinput>, <userinput>gox</userinput>, <userinput>goy</"
"userinput>, <userinput>canvassize</userinput> and <userinput>penwidth</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Paljud käsud vajavad sisendina pikslite arvu: <userinput>forward</"
"userinput>, <userinput>backward</userinput>, <userinput>go</userinput>, "
"<userinput>gox</userinput>, <userinput>goy</userinput>, "
"<userinput>canvassize</userinput> ja <userinput>penwidth</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In early versions of &kturtle; the canvas was essentially a raster image, "
"yet for recent versions the canvas is a vector drawing. This means that the "
"canvas can be zoomed in and out, therefore a pixel does not necessarily have "
"to translate to one dot on the screen."
msgstr ""
"&kturtle;'i varasemates versioonides oli lõuend põhimõtteliselt rasterpilt, "
"nüüd aga on see vektorjoonistus. See tähendab, et lõuendit saab suurendada "
"ja vähendada, sest piksel ei pea tingimata vastama ühele punktile ekraanil."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "RGB combinations (color codes)"
msgstr "RGB värvikoodid"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"RGB combinations are used to describe colors. The <quote>R</quote> stand for "
"<quote>red</quote>, the <quote>G</quote> stands for <quote>green</quote> and "
"the <quote>B</quote> stands for <quote>blue</quote>. An example of an RGB "
"combination is <userinput>255,0,0</userinput>: the first value (<quote>red</"
"quote>) is 255 and the others are 0, so this represents a bright shade of "
"red. Each value of an RGB combination has to be in the range 0 to 255. Here "
"a small list of some often used colors:"
msgstr ""
"RGB värvikoodid tähistavad värve. <quote>R<quote> tähendab punast (inglise "
"keeles <quote>red</quote>), <quote>G</quote> rohelist (<quote>green</quote>) "
"ja <quote>B</quote> sinist (</quote>blue</quote>). RGB värvikood on näiteks "
"<userinput>255,0,0</userinput>, kus esimene ehk punane väärtus on 255 ja "
"teised 0, mis kokku annab erepunase. Iga RGB värvikoodi väärtus peab olema "
"vahemikus 0 kuni 255. Toome siin ära mõned sagedamini kasutust leidvad "
"värvid:"

